<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,1370,1748]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
REMARKS: Verrall 
<emphasis box="[377,400,1566,1591]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">in</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Scudder, S. H." box="[408,638,1566,1592]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 376" refId="ref149640" refString="Scudder, S. H. (1882) Nomenclator zoologicus. An alphabetical list of all generic names that have been employed by naturalists for recent and fossil animals from the earliest times to the close of the year 1879. I. Supplemental list of genera in zoology. List of generic names employed in zoology and paleontology to the close of the year 1879, chiefly supplemental to those catalogued by Agassiz and Marschall, or indexed in the Zoological Record. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 19 [i], i - xxi, 1 - 376. [August] [Recorded in the August issue of American Journal of Science.]" type="journal article" year="1882">Scudder (1882: 71)</bibRefCitation>
listed the spelling 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrall" authorityYear="1882" box="[865,1010,1566,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Chlorosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[865,1010,1566,1591]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Chlorosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and this was cited as an unjustified emendation by 
<bibRefCitation author="Woodley, N. E." box="[432,691,1605,1631]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="26" refId="ref153756" refString="Woodley, N. E. (2001) A world catalog of the Stratiomyidae (Insecta, Diptera). Myia, 11, 473 + [1] pp. [after 26 February] [Date of postscript.]" type="journal article" year="2001">Woodley (2001: 202)</bibRefCitation>
, but criteria for making this name available as an emendation were not found to be fulfilled in 
<bibRefCitation author="Scudder, S. H." box="[648,836,1644,1670]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 376" refId="ref149640" refString="Scudder, S. H. (1882) Nomenclator zoologicus. An alphabetical list of all generic names that have been employed by naturalists for recent and fossil animals from the earliest times to the close of the year 1879. I. Supplemental list of genera in zoology. List of generic names employed in zoology and paleontology to the close of the year 1879, chiefly supplemental to those catalogued by Agassiz and Marschall, or indexed in the Zoological Record. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 19 [i], i - xxi, 1 - 376. [August] [Recorded in the August issue of American Journal of Science.]" type="journal article" year="1882">Scudder (1882)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Verrall, 1882" authorityName="Verrall" authorityYear="1882" box="[850,1164,1644,1670]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Chlorosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[850,995,1644,1669]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Chlorosoma</emphasis>
Verrall, 1882
</taxonomicName>
is thus an unavailable name, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[325,456,1683,1709]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">new status</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
